title: DAY-Shift Report 2/19/2022 Sat
text: PROGRAM: SPEAR to BEAMS delivering 500mA to users with top-off every 5 mins. BEAMLINES: All open. 0814 Opened BL16-2 for remote operations. FAULTS: None reported. EXPERIMENTS: 0540-0605 BL2-1 user support. Detector is showing unexpected peaks. Removed sample and confirmed no peaks, issue is with sample alignment. Tried aligning sample in y and theta but no change to the plot. BL staff came in and assisted later in the morning. OPERATIONS: 0800-1700 No phone interruptions during planned SLAC PBX maintenance. 0802 BL2-2 laser safety key issued to user.

title: CATER 155270, Kly Mod 11-2: excessive jitter.

text: Swing shift 1st routine walk through complete. Hutch 1.2 N2 dewar weights and pressure recorded.

title: * Re: re-inserted UNDS 34 > Restored UNDS 33 as well.
Rephasing all klystrons in L2, most are off by 10-20 degrees thus far
FACET beam spontaneously disappeared
* Re: FACET beam spontaneously disappeared
text: Beam is still present in the injector but dies before it gets into DL10. All of the injector RF looks okay and I don't see any evidence that the laser changed substantially.

title: * Re: FACET beam spontaneously disappeared
text: Beam is still present in the injector but dies before it gets into DL10. All of the injector RF looks okay and I don't see any evidence that the laser changed substantially. No visible magnet issues. Baffling so far.

title: * Re: FACET beam spontaneously disappeared
text: I was able to fix the orbit up to DL10 by moving L0B's phase by ~50 degrees. However, the beam still doesn't get into the dogleg.

title: Was able to get the beam through DL10 by turning the bends down from 125 --> 111 MeV
text: Will try rephasing the injector RF now.

title: Looks like 10-4's phase jumped by about 90 degrees
text: I empirically moved 10-4's phase around until I maximized the beam energy. Very confusingly, the WVG phase (blue trace on the plot below) didn't see the jump at all and is now reading very differently. However, the SLED phase (red trace) did see the jump and is now back where it was previously after my manual phase wozzling. No idea how to explain all that. We're standardizing the DL10 bends now and we'll rephase the injector stations again when that's finished.

title: FACET recovered, back to phase scans
TMO requests we restore UNDS 26-32
Finally finished phase scanning L2, re-chirped LI14, steady beam through BC14 now.
text: We are now able to stay on energy in BC14. This is due to some combination of rephasing klystrons and us gaining energy as it gets cooler out. We did no phase scans in L3, but we now have too much energy - we didn't have enough (with the same complement) a few hours ago when we lost all the transmission in the early afternoon. This leads me to believe that the day-night energy variation is the source of our problems more than stations being misphased.

title: Day Shift HRS-Log
text: 02/19/22 14:00 - Randy Hollis - C0 (common) - HRS.AX.VG-Gathered parts and documentation for oil processor pump rebuild 02/19/22 14:00 - Randy Hollis - C0 (common) - HRS.00.00-Completed organization of vacuum hardware 02/19/22 13:20 - Roland Evans - C2 - HRS.CS.EL-Well back on the Main compressor station VFD's! I came up with a work around for IT security & firewall issues for loading drive configurations. I downloaded the software onto my personal laptop & connected it to VFD drive C1, It connected to the drive on 1st attempt. I was able to see the current configuration, at that point I was able to retrieve the configurations from the LP, MP & HP drives that we currently use. I moved the power adapter to each machine & uploaded the configurations to C2-Compressors 1, 2, 3, & 4. I will configure C5 & 6 tomorrow. We should probably buy a (clean PC) for task such as this. We have several devices in the field that doesn't do well with firewalls & heavy IT security protocols. Off shift, the middle of the night, weekends or holidays this could cause downtime if we can't talk to devices. NOTE: adjusting taper when pulling upstream undulators
text: TMO has made several requests that we pull undulators starting upstream, which complicates things by changing the starting K, which will cause the photon energy to be slightly off. We can fix this by adjusting the taper of the remaining undulators by a constant. The process is as follows: (1) Pull any requested upstream undulators (2) From the ULT GUI open "+ Taper Control" (3) One the left hand side, find the starting K of the new "first" segment (3) subtract that from the desired starting K calculted by ULT (4) In "+ Taper Control", plug that number into the "constant" field of the "Taper by difference" (5) Select the cells you want to adjust in the "New destination" table on the left hand side (6) Click "Calcualte" - you should see the K values in the table update (7) Click "Move K Selected" to adjust the undulators (8) As a sanity check, open the first cell in UNDS > Coll/Motion and verify that the "ACT K" is correct
